00:09:21.978 --> 00:09:23.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

151
00:09:26.691 --> 00:09:31.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Zeppole di... San Gius...

152
00:09:44.333 --> 00:09:46.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Eric] <i>Boris,</i>
<i>what's your current location?</i>

153
00:09:46.419 --> 00:09:47.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Is Keith with you?!</i>

154
00:09:49.005 --> 00:09:50.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, he's here!

155
00:09:51.048 --> 00:09:52.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're northbound on Route 8!

156
00:09:52.967 --> 00:09:55.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Route 8?</i>
<i>Why are you out there?</i>

157
00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:58.264 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No idea! Take it up with Keith!

158
00:09:58.347 --> 00:10:00.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[screaming]

159
00:10:07.273 --> 00:10:09.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Keith, we have</i>
<i>an emergency on our hands!</i>

160
00:10:09.567 --> 00:10:11.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-Get back here immediately!</i>
-Hmm?

161
00:10:11.527 --> 00:10:14.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The gas was released</i>
<i>throughout the tower.</i>

162
00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:16.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?! Run that by me again!

163
00:10:16.616 --> 00:10:19.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We can't get ahold</i>
<i>of any of our people</i>

164
00:10:19.201 --> 00:10:20.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>who were inside the building!</i>

165
00:10:20.661 --> 00:10:22.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Genie, we have to head back!
-[Eric continuing]

166
00:10:22.955 --> 00:10:24.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Don't worry.
-[yelps]

167
00:10:24.123 --> 00:10:25.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[car horn honking]

168
00:10:25.291 --> 00:10:27.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Keith] Sorry, Eric.
Deal with it yourself.

169
00:10:27.293 --> 00:10:29.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are you talking about,
you idiot?!

170
00:10:29.295 --> 00:10:31.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lily and the kids are in there.

171
00:10:31.297 --> 00:10:32.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Keith] If <i>it's been released.</i>

172
00:10:33.007 --> 00:10:35.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[gasps]
-If it has been released,

173
00:10:35.843 --> 00:10:37.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
then the gas is fake,

174
00:10:37.595 --> 00:10:40.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a dispersal meant
to throw the scene into chaos.

175
00:10:40.181 --> 00:10:44.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>They're trying to buy time and</i>
<i>probably cover their escape.</i>

176
00:10:44.560 --> 00:10:45.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where's your proof?

177
00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:47.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Keith] Didn't you see it?

178
00:10:47.355 --> 00:10:49.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The criminal
is a myopic thinker,

179
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:50.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
an immature narcissist.

180
00:10:50.858 --> 00:10:53.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's your basic
dumb, self-absorbed kid

181
00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:55.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
obsessed with
superficial aesthetics.

182
00:10:55.571 --> 00:10:57.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's harsh, even for you.

183
00:10:57.615 --> 00:11:00.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When a narcissist is writing
his autobiography,

184
00:11:00.493 --> 00:11:03.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
his death is
a critical component.

185
00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:04.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Slowly dying in agony</i>

186
00:11:05.081 --> 00:11:08.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>as his skin blisters</i>
<i>from a modified corrosive gas,</i>

187
00:11:08.292 --> 00:11:11.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you think he'd be okay
going out like that?

188
00:11:11.087 --> 00:11:12.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look through
the old profiles again.

189
00:11:12.880 --> 00:11:14.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nothing's there. Doesn't happen.

190
00:11:16.008 --> 00:11:17.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Eric] <i>You might be right.</i>

191
00:11:17.676 --> 00:11:19.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Everything you've said</i>
<i>is still just a theory.</i>

192
00:11:19.970 --> 00:11:23.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The fact of the matter is</i>
<i>we can't contact anyone inside.</i>

193
00:11:23.641 --> 00:11:26.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a knockout gas, Eric.
Come on.

194
00:11:26.727 --> 00:11:31.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>This incident and the IFV theft</i>
<i>have the same structure.</i>

195
00:11:31.107 --> 00:11:34.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>A sophisticated mind is working</i>
<i>toward another objective</i>

196
00:11:34.568 --> 00:11:36.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>under the cover of this chaos.</i>

197
00:11:38.280 --> 00:11:41.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In other words, some group
is leeching off of crimes

198
00:11:41.158 --> 00:11:43.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to carry out their own
carefully planned ones.

199
00:11:43.744 --> 00:11:47.039 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come to think of it, they might
even be manipulating crimes

200
00:11:47.123 --> 00:11:49.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that seem
like random occurrences.

201
00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:52.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A cycle of madness
is getting ready to break out.

202
00:11:52.962 --> 00:11:55.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We won't find our answers
on the surface,

203
00:11:55.923 --> 00:11:57.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>but behind the scenes.</i>

204
00:11:57.800 --> 00:11:59.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SOMEONE IS COMMITTING
MEANINGLESS CRIMES

205
00:11:59.260 --> 00:12:01.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
FOR THE SOLE PURPOSE
OF LURING OUT B.

206
00:12:04.265 --> 00:12:05.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're late.

207
00:12:05.891 --> 00:12:08.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kamui wouldn't leave
until he made his stupid trash.

208
00:12:08.894 --> 00:12:11.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But the boys
were so excited about it,

209
00:12:11.188 --> 00:12:14.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as they were able to bring
their lamentable lives to an end

210
00:12:14.608 --> 00:12:16.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as part
of my magnificent collection.

211
00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:19.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That means they were pathetic
to the very end, weren't they?

212
00:12:19.488 --> 00:12:21.031 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

213
00:12:21.115 --> 00:12:24.201 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kamui, you haven't forgotten
about our objective, I trust?

214
00:12:24.285 --> 00:12:27.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course not.
That was just playtime.

215
00:12:27.621 --> 00:12:30.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The objective
was accomplished just fine.

216
00:12:33.294 --> 00:12:35.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And yet I don't see him
here with us.

217
00:12:35.963 --> 00:12:38.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've selective hearing
regarding my orders,

218
00:12:38.799 --> 00:12:40.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a bad habit.

219
00:12:40.968 --> 00:12:42.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, yeah.

220
00:12:42.511 --> 00:12:44.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, Minatsuki,
do we really have to lug

221
00:12:44.972 --> 00:12:47.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the black-winged king
all the way back with us?

222
00:12:47.558 --> 00:12:50.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. Those are our orders.

223
00:12:50.811 --> 00:12:53.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And do we have
to bring him back alive?

224
00:12:59.278 --> 00:13:01.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. That's all we want.

225
00:13:14.043 --> 00:13:18.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I welcome you to Divine Days.

226
00:13:18.297 --> 00:13:20.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A few days every October,

227
00:13:20.466 --> 00:13:23.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Lake Lenan becomes
a gateway to the kingdom of God.

228
00:13:23.302 --> 00:13:26.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Souls dance with joy
in the dark.

229
00:13:27.014 --> 00:13:28.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[splashing]

230
00:13:30.893 --> 00:13:32.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[singer vocalizing]

231
00:13:33.854 --> 00:13:35.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn't it beautiful,

232
00:13:36.065 --> 00:13:38.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
countless lights
in the darkness?

233
00:13:39.443 --> 00:13:41.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I absolutely love this place.

234
00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:44.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just one little light
can be enough

235
00:13:44.532 --> 00:13:48.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to keep you from fearing
the dark or losing your way.

236
00:13:48.202 --> 00:13:51.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you understand
what I'm trying to tell you?

237
00:13:51.789 --> 00:13:53.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Light represents hope.

238
00:13:53.707 --> 00:13:56.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can save your nonsense.

239
00:13:56.168 --> 00:13:57.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell me where she is!

240
00:13:57.962 --> 00:14:01.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you don't start talking
right now, I'll kill you!

241
00:14:01.257 --> 00:14:03.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My, you're so easy to read.

242
00:14:03.592 --> 00:14:05.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is she...

243
00:14:05.344 --> 00:14:06.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
your light?

244
00:14:06.595 --> 00:14:09.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are even your cherished
memories of her vague?

245
00:14:09.557 --> 00:14:10.933 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let me guess.

246
00:14:11.016 --> 00:14:13.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't know much
about yourself either, do you?

247
00:14:13.602 --> 00:14:17.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's why I can hear your
desperate shouting so clearly.

248
00:14:17.940 --> 00:14:20.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Look at me! I'm right here!

249
00:14:20.776 --> 00:14:23.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You see?! I'm alive! I'm alive!

250
00:14:23.696 --> 00:14:25.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Somebody find me!"

251
00:14:27.741 --> 00:14:29.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

252
00:14:36.125 --> 00:14:37.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hate to tell you this,

253
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:41.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but the only things here are us
and the spirits of the dead.

254
00:14:41.422 --> 00:14:43.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Out of all of us,
I'm the only one

255
00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:46.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who's actually spent time
with you, however briefly.

256
00:14:46.802 --> 00:14:51.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There was even a time
I lived only for you.

257
00:14:51.265 --> 00:14:53.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We watched
these very lights together.

258
00:14:53.726 --> 00:14:56.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's the reason why I
lured you all the way here.

259
00:14:56.854 --> 00:14:59.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I wanted to make you remember.
-[gasps]

260
00:15:11.118 --> 00:15:14.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, dear. There go all my hopes.

261
00:15:14.830 --> 00:15:16.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's depressing.

262
00:15:16.582 --> 00:15:17.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Koku...

263
00:15:19.126 --> 00:15:20.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've been thinking lately

264
00:15:20.878 --> 00:15:24.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about the identity of the person
who locked away your memories.

265
00:15:31.597 --> 00:15:33.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

266
00:15:33.432 --> 00:15:36.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've figured it out at last.

267
00:15:39.021 --> 00:15:40.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell me where she is.

268
00:15:43.651 --> 00:15:46.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The one who locked away
all of those memories

269
00:15:46.820 --> 00:15:48.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was none other than...

270
00:15:48.781 --> 00:15:50.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you, yourself.

271
00:15:51.575 --> 00:15:54.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I bet you wanted
to forget it all...

272
00:15:55.287 --> 00:15:57.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
everything that happened
that day...

273
00:15:58.916 --> 00:16:00.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
everything.

274
00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:02.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
However...

275
00:16:05.506 --> 00:16:09.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if you think you can forget me,
you're dead wrong.

276
00:16:09.301 --> 00:16:10.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[slurps]

277
00:16:10.511 --> 00:16:12.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I won't let you,

278
00:16:12.304 --> 00:16:15.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I'll never forgive you
for not choosing me!

279
00:16:19.478 --> 00:16:21.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Keith] Where the heck is this?

280
00:16:21.313 --> 00:16:23.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How should I know?
-Hmph.

281
00:16:24.608 --> 00:16:27.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So do you mind filling me in?

282
00:16:27.361 --> 00:16:30.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What in the world
are you chasing after, Keith?

283
00:16:31.615 --> 00:16:32.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not sure.

284
00:16:32.866 --> 00:16:33.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

285
00:16:34.034 --> 00:16:37.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's just something
I need to chase down.

286
00:16:37.413 --> 00:16:41.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, but what are
you chasing down?

287
00:16:41.500 --> 00:16:44.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't know. I wish I knew.

288
00:17:37.931 --> 00:17:40.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[shudders]

289
00:17:50.694 --> 00:17:53.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do yourself a favor,
and cut off my left leg.

290
00:17:53.781 --> 00:17:55.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It'll be useful to you someday.

291
00:17:58.994 --> 00:18:01.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Touch Canopus.

292
00:18:02.956 --> 00:18:04.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do that, and...

293
00:18:06.502 --> 00:18:07.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Koku] Canopus?

294
00:18:14.134 --> 00:18:15.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman groans]

295
00:18:18.347 --> 00:18:20.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can you tell me your name?

296
00:18:20.224 --> 00:18:24.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Zeppole... di San Giuseppe.

297
00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:27.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know
where you are right now, miss?

298
00:18:27.272 --> 00:18:28.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm...

299
00:18:29.608 --> 00:18:31.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps, yells]

300
00:18:31.985 --> 00:18:33.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[overlapping chatter]

301
00:18:33.529 --> 00:18:34.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Lily gasping]

302
00:18:38.659 --> 00:18:40.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Careful not
to sit up so quickly.

303
00:18:40.661 --> 00:18:41.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you feeling queasy?

304
00:18:41.870 --> 00:18:43.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any discomfort?

305
00:18:43.622 --> 00:18:45.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're alive?

306
00:18:45.582 --> 00:18:47.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I remember seeing gas
flood into the room,

307
00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:49.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but nothing after that.

308
00:18:49.169 --> 00:18:51.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They say it was
just knockout gas.

309
00:18:51.547 --> 00:18:55.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But one thing's for sure.
They got us good this time.

310
00:18:55.717 --> 00:18:58.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lily] So you're saying
our whack-job of a perp

311
00:18:58.303 --> 00:18:59.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was bluffing the entire time?

312
00:18:59.763 --> 00:19:03.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, no. There's apparently
evidence to the contrary.

313
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:06.353 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What does that mean?

314
00:19:06.436 --> 00:19:08.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It means they did find
the poison gas.

315
00:19:08.730 --> 00:19:11.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They just didn't use it
for some reason.

316
00:19:11.608 --> 00:19:13.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-But, uh...
-Hmm?

317
00:19:14.736 --> 00:19:18.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Mario] The way they found it
wasn't exactly normal.

318
00:19:21.618 --> 00:19:23.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gags]

319
00:19:36.175 --> 00:19:37.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Looks like we just missed 'em.

320
00:19:51.690 --> 00:19:53.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[distant sirens]

321
00:19:54.026 --> 00:19:55.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Brandon] In addition
to the criminals' skins,

322
00:19:56.028 --> 00:19:57.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they've also found
their remains.

323
00:19:57.905 --> 00:19:59.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Lily] Where?
-Uh...

324
00:19:59.948 --> 00:20:03.076 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think you're better off
not knowing. If I told you,

325
00:20:03.160 --> 00:20:05.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it'd probably make you lose
your appetite for a while.

326
00:20:07.039 --> 00:20:10.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See, this ominous feeling
has been nagging at me.

327
00:20:10.375 --> 00:20:11.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Hmm?
-Hmm?

328
00:20:11.460 --> 00:20:13.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[overlapping chatter]

329
00:20:13.086 --> 00:20:16.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lily] <i>Don't these latest cases</i>
<i>seem a bit strange to you?</i>

330
00:20:16.673 --> 00:20:18.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I mean, as far as I know,</i>

331
00:20:18.884 --> 00:20:21.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we didn't get any answers
in this case, either, right?

332
00:20:21.845 --> 00:20:25.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I feel like something strange
is going on in this city.

333
00:20:25.641 --> 00:20:27.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[distant sirens]
-You get all serious for once,

334
00:20:28.060 --> 00:20:31.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and that's what you choose
to talk about?

335
00:20:31.355 --> 00:20:33.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
